dsDescriptionValue.value:
This is a 9-item mood scale. It was also administered in CAPS/85 and CAPS/86. In CAPS/87, the scale followed BONUS6 and BONUS7, which manipulated the R's receipt of individual and team bonuses (see those units for detail). In CAPS/88, the scale proceeded BONUS 4-8 (see those units for detail).

Consists of responses to 9, 11-point scale items measuring mood. Three composite measures have been created (all items scored as administered, except item 5, which is reverse scored for these comp osites): (1) total over all 9 items, (2) present mood, and (3) future outlook.

Scaling information: *(FEEL5 reverse score) TOTMOOD=average of (FEEL1+FEEL2+FEEL3+FEEL4+*FEEL5+FEEL6+FEEL7+FEEL8+FEEL9) PRESMOOD= average of (FEEL1+FEEL2+FEEL3+FEEL4+*FEEL5) FUTRMOOD= average of (FEEL6+FEEL7+FEEL8+FEEL9)

publicationCitation.value: Schwarz, N., and Clore, G. L. (1983) Mood, Misattribution, and Judgements of Well-Being: Informative and Directive Functions of Affective States. Journal of Personality and Social Psychology, 45, 513-523.
